==English==
===Expression===
'''[[I]] [[don't]] [[think]] [[so]]'''

#I think that what has just been said is untrue, but I am not completely sure.
#:''Is this the right place to catch the bus? &mdash; I don't think so.''
#(''sarcastic'') No (''used to refuse or decline something proposed'').
#:''Go out with you?  Huh, I don't think so, sweetheart!''

====Synonyms====

*(''I think that what has just been said is untrue''): [[I think not]]
*(''no''): [[absolutely not]], [[hardly]], [[not in a million years]], [[not on your life]], [[not on your nelly]] (''British''), [[not likely]], [[no way]], [[no way Jose]], [[as if]]

